spanGrp.span: sok ih nge Ilson ... Ilson Magekon
nem blong mi Ilson ... Ilson Magekon
my name is Ilson, Ilson Magekon
ngyo nam longbini nap pune punen soo usilii basee ngyee
mi mi wantem talem wan stori abaot ol pijin
I want to tell a story about birds
punen kiye usilii basee ngyee basee ngyee lam van ka lap gyeh
stori ya abaot ol pijin ol pijin oli go blong wok
this story is about birds, the birds went to work
a punen, punen kiye me van momelé
be stori ya i go olsem
and the story goes as follows
wan taem soo [wobuong soo] wip mane
wip mwe kye basee kekevene lap mee
nawimba i singaot everi pijin oli kam
Pigeon called all birds to come
ngale mwe kie mane ngyee mwe kie ka
afta i talem long olgeta i talem se
and then he said to them, he said
bwiya mo longbini ka dap van dap koot ne san too
nambilak i wantem yumi go yumi prasem karen blong hem
Rail wants that we go to clean his garden
o.k. lam lingi wobuong en monok
o.k. oli putum taem blong hem finis
lam lingi wobuong en monok lam van
oli putum taem blong em finis oli go
they set a date, they went
lam mee lan wobuong en lam van lam koot
oli kam long taem blong em, oli go oli pras
they came to the date, they went to clean (the gardens)
lam van, a basee kekevene lam neknak ne aa meleh soo me van mwe páne an wesisi
oli go, mo everi pijin oli redi blong ol kakae blong olgeta, wan i go i rusum wael yam blong hem
they went, and all birds prepared their food, one roasted his wild yam
soo mwe van mwi idi meleh minyeh ngyee
wan i go i tekem narafela kakae
ngyee kevene lam neknak ne aa meleh
olgeta everiwan oli redi long kakae blong olgeta
a be meerin basee ngyee lare mestim patomo, batomo me saa fren [biibilien]
afta bifo ol pijin oli no mestim rat, rat em i fren blong olgeta
now, before the birds did not avoid Rat, Rat was their friend
batomo mwe pwet lantan, basee ngyee lam du lamwiye
rat i stap long graon, ol pijin oli stap antap
Rat lives on the ground, the birds live above
lam van, lam van lap koot lam kie batomo mu duusilii ngyee
oli go, oli go, oli pras, rat i folem olgeta
they went, they went to clean (the garden), Rat followed them
lam van, maa maa ngye mwe páne kooko pipili
oli go, sotleg, em i rusum red popile
they went, Dove, he/she had roasted red yam
me pinin koro, an kooko pipili monok, mo syungane lon san aróówoo
i rusum gud, red popile blong hem finis, i fulum ap long basket blong hem
he roasted it well, his red yam finished, he put it into his basket
a batome me mee, ngye món, batomo mu duusilii ngyee a tere páne an meleh
be rat i kam, em tu, rat i folem olgeta, be i no rusum kakae blong hem
but Rat came, he too, rat followed them, he had not roasted his food
they workd, worked, worked and went on
lam kootse, lam kootse se bwiya ngiye
oli bras blong, oli bras blong nambilak ya
they cleaned, they cleaned for Pigeon
lam koot se bwiya, lam gyeh van, máá mwe kyet
oli pras blong nambilak, oli wok i go, oli hanggri
they cleaned for Pigeon, they worked on, they got hungry
lam du lam gyeh van ngabe, a batomo mwe tinyam
oli stap oli wok i go festaem, be rat i haed
they went on working at first, but the rat was hiding
mwe kie, ee, nam van nap min we bwe
i talem, ee, mi go dring wota festaem
he said, hello, I will first drink water
mu kuo selaa van mwe sek lon saa aróówoo ngyee
i ron i go i lus i lukaot long ol basket blong olgeta
he went away and looked in their baskets
tééne aa meleh ngyee van me van lon aróówoo se maa mwe lehe ke
i lukaot ol kakae blong olgeta i go i go long basket blong sotleg i luk we
he saw their food that went in the basket of Dove, he saw that
maa mwe páne an kooko pipili mwe pwet
sotleg i rusum red popile blong hem i stap
mwe van ma ane muru buk
i go i kakae smol festaem
he went and ate a little bit at first
mwe kuo me van me lehe ngyee teteh lam koot
i ron i go i luk olgeta bakaken, oli pras
he ran back and saw the others, they cleaned (the garden)
lam du lam koot van, mw kie
oli stap oli pras i go, i talem
they were cleaning the garden, he said
myaa ma are mwi teteh mwe kie ka
e nap van, nap van nap min we muru món bwe
e, mi go mi go mi drink smol wota festaem
I will go, I will go drink a bit at first
mwe spid van teteh, me van, ma ane kooko pipili e maa teteh
i hariap i go bakaken, i go, i kakae red popile blong sotleg bakaken
he went quickly again, he went, he ate (from) the red yam of Dove again
du mwe tibyak ne kooko kiye van, envini kooko e maa
i stap mekem popile ya i go, i flatem popile blong sotleg
he worked hard on this yam, he ate all of the yam of Dove
monok, lam gyeh van, wip mwe kie, monok!
finis, oli wok i go, nawimba i talem, finis!
this fiished, they worked, Pigeon said, finish!
lam van momele, lam van lon saa aróówoo ngyee, lam van lam sek lon saa aróówoo ngyee
oli go olsem, oli go long ol basket blong olgeta, oli go oli jek long ol basket blong olgeta
they went like that, they went to their baskets, they went they checked their baskets
musyoo mane basee minyeh ngyee mane lela
sam wetem narafela pijin olsem nalaklak
some with other birds, like the Silvereye
syideda lam van lon saa aróówoo ngyee, lam sógo
grin pijin oli go long basket blong olgeta, oli tekem
Green Pigeon, they went into their baskets, they took...
aa meleh ngyee lam mee lam ane, a maa me van lon san aróówoo
ol kakae blong olgeta i kam, oli kakae, be sotleg i go long basket blong hem
their food, they came and ate, but Dove went into his basket,
mwe sek van lon san aróówoo, me lehe ke
i jek i go long basket blong hem, i luk we
he checked out his basket, he saw that...
ee, ok meleh me selaa, vanten soo me lah ne
ee, kakae blong mi i lus, wan man i stilim
oh, my food is missing, someone stole it
kiye sok biibilien soo me lahne
emya wan fren blong mi i stilim
he, one of my friends, stole it
momelé me van me lehe wip
olsem i go i luk nawimba
so he went and saw Pigeon
i stap long basket blong mi
vanten adyee soo me mee me lahne
wan man blong yumi i kam i stilim
one person of us came and stole it
momelé wip mwe kie, mo, nap kye adyee kevene dyep mee sógóó
olsem nawimba i talem, i gud, mi singaot yumi everiwan i kam tugeta
so Pigeon said, good, I will call everyone of us to come together
mwe kie ngyee lap mee teteh mwe, sye mwe lah ne meleh e maa lon san aróówoo
i talem oli kam bakaken i talem, hu i stilim kakae blong sotleg long basket blong hem
he ordered them to come again, he said, who stole the food of Dove in his basket?
momelé wip mwe wisi ne maa, Maa, meleh sówe nge
olsem nawimba i askem long sotleg, sotleg, wanem kakae
so Pigeon asked Dove, Dove, which food (did you have)?
meleh sówe nge kom páne kom idi mee dap gyeh meten ka kop ane tabuyaa
wanem kakae yu rusum yu tekem i kam yumi wok i blong yu kakae long medelde
what was the food that you roasted and took with you to our work so that you eat it at midday?
maa mwe kie ka, nam páne kooko pipili
sotleg i talem mi rusum red popile
Dove said tthat, I roasted red yam
mwe kie, moo, et kevene dap dap ngiri luwot ngyee adap sogave pat ngyee
i talem, ale, yumi everiwan yumi soem ol tut blong yumi mo yumi openem ol maot blong yumi
he [Pigeon] said, good, everyone of us should show their teeth, open your mouths
ngyee kevene lam sogave paa ngyee
olgeta everiwan oli openem maot blong olgeta
wip me téé lon... lon paa ngyee
nawimba i luk insaed long ol maot blong olgeta
Pigenon lookd inside the mouths of them
me mee me van lon basee soo buk me téévan lon pan me lehe ee
i kam i go long wan pijin festaem i luk i go long maot blong hem i luk, ee
he came, he went inside... one bird first he looked into the mouth, he looked, okay
mu duusilii basee kevene me téé lon paa ngyee tere lehe
i folem everi pijin i luk long maot blong olgeta, i no luk
he followed every bird, he looked into their mouths, he did not see (anything)
te mee mwe lehe batomo mo kóókóógóló pan a mwe syatan pwet
i kam i luk rat i satem maot blong hem be i bendaon i stap
he came and saw Rat kept his mouth shut, and was bending down
batomo me téé me lamwiye, mwe kie
rat i luk i kam antap i talem
Rat i look up, he said
the teeth are clenched, open your mouth!
batomo mwe kyetgare luwen gon mo pwet
rat i kakae tut blong em i stap
i kakae tut blong hem nomo i stap
kom mas songave pan, ke songave pan kyem lehe ke
yu mas openem maot blong yu, taem i openem maot oli luk we
you have to open your mouth, when you open your mouth, we will see that...
batomo kiye ma ane kooko pipili e maa
rat ya i kakae red popile blong sotleg
the rat had eaten the red yam of Dove
luwen ngyee me pili, a minyan mi pili
ol tut blong hem i red, mo tang blong hem i red
his teeth were red, and his tongue was red
kyem kie, ngyak gon kom du kom lah lon sadyee aróówoo ngyee
oli talem, yu nomo yu stap stil long basket blong yumi
they said, it was you who was stole from our baskets
kyem komane batomo kiye gon batomo kiye mo kuo me van
oli ronem rat ya nomo, rat ya i ron i go
they chased Rat, Rat ran away
now it is finished, Spit out!
